-- Narrowed postulate: symmetric-monoidal coherence on the structural
-- fragment, at the `FreeMonoidal` level.
--
-- This is the *minimal* postulate needed to discharge the original
-- `decode-rel-resp-‚âÖ·¥¥-atomic-compound-0E`.  It is the statement of
-- Mac Lane's symmetric monoidal coherence theorem on the structural
-- (i.e. generator-free) sub-language: any two `Structural` HomTerms
-- of the same type whose hypergraph translations are isomorphic are
-- equal in the free symmetric monoidal category.
--
-- All `decode-rel`/`bridge`/`unflatten`-flavoured plumbing has been
-- factored out: the postulate conclusion is the plain `_‚âàTerm_`
-- equality between two `HomTerm A B`s built from
-- `id, Œª‚áí, Œª‚áê, œÅ‚áí, œÅ‚áê, Œ±‚áí, Œ±‚áê, œÉ, _‚àò_, _‚äó‚ÇÅ_`.  The constructive
-- discharge ultimately requires extending
-- `Categories.MonoidalCoherence.Solver` (currently Mac Lane only) to
-- handle œÉ via permutation tracking ‚Äî see the header for the path.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Extract the underlying permutation of a structural HomTerm.
--
-- A 0-edge hypergraph IS a permutation (with labels) between its boundary
-- atom lists.  We extract this permutation by structural induction on
-- `Structural`, using only the propositional permutation combinators
-- (`refl`, `prep`, `swap`, `trans`) and standard list-permutation lemmas
-- (`++-comm`, `++-assoc`, `++-identity ≥`, `++‚Å∫`).
--
-- The directions:
--   * `id        : A ‚Üí A`              ‚Ü¶ refl
--   * `Œª‚áí : I‚äóA ‚Üí A`,  `Œª‚áê : A ‚Üí I‚äóA`  ‚Ü¶ refl     ([] ++ xs ‚â° xs definitionally)
--   * `œÅ‚áí : A‚äóI ‚Üí A`                   ‚Ü¶ ++-identity ≥
--   * `œÅ‚áê : A ‚Üí A‚äóI`                   ‚Ü¶ sym (++-identity ≥)
--   * `Œ±‚áí : (A‚äóB)‚äóC ‚Üí A‚äó(B‚äóC)`         ‚Ü¶ ‚Ü≠-reflexive (++-assoc)
--   * `Œ±‚áê : A‚äó(B‚äóC) ‚Üí (A‚äóB)‚äóC`         ‚Ü¶ sym
--   * `œÉ  : A‚äóB ‚Üí B‚äóA`                 ‚Ü¶ ++-comm
--   * `_‚àò_`                            ‚Ü¶ Perm.trans (note: h ‚àò k goes k then h)
--   * `_‚äó‚ÇÅ_`                           ‚Ü¶ PermProp.++‚Å∫

Structural-to-perm
  : ‚àÄ {A B} {f : HomTerm A B}
  ‚Üí Structural f ‚Üí flatten A ‚Ü≠ flatten B
Structural-to-perm (structural-id {A}) = Perm.refl
Structural-to-perm structural-Œª‚áí        = Perm.refl
Structural-to-perm structural-Œª‚áê        = Perm.refl
Structural-to-perm (structural-œÅ‚áí {A})  = PermProp.++-identity ≥ (flatten A)
Structural-to-perm (structural-œÅ‚áê {A})  = Perm.‚Ü≠-sym (PermProp.++-identity ≥ (flatten A))
Structural-to-perm (structural-Œ±‚áí {A} {B} {C}) =
  Perm.‚Ü≠-reflexive (Data.List.Properties.++-assoc (flatten A) (flatten B) (flatten C))
Structural-to-perm (structural-Œ±‚áê {A} {B} {C}) =
  Perm.‚Ü≠-sym (Perm.‚Ü≠-reflexive (Data.List.Properties.++-assoc (flatten A) (flatten B) (flatten C)))
Structural-to-perm (structural-œÉ {A} {B}) =
  PermProp.++-comm (flatten A) (flatten B)
Structural-to-perm (structural-‚àò sh sk) =
  Perm.trans (Structural-to-perm sk) (Structural-to-perm sh)
Structural-to-perm (structural-‚äó sh sk) =
  PermProp.++‚Å∫ (Structural-to-perm sh) (Structural-to-perm sk)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Narrowed postulate: symmetric-monoidal coherence on the structural
-- fragment.
--
-- An earlier version of this file attempted a further split into
--
--   * `perm-eq-from-iso : ‚ü™ f ‚ü´ ‚âÖ·¥¥ ‚ü™ g ‚ü´ ‚Üí Structural-to-perm sf ‚â° Structural-to-perm sg`
--   * `Structural-coherence-from-perm-eq : ‚Ä¶ ‚â° ‚Ä¶ ‚Üí f ‚âàTerm g`
--
-- and derived `Structural-coherence-‚âàTerm` from the two.  That split
-- is **unsound** in its propositional-equality form:
-- `Data.List.Relation.Binary.Permutation.Propositional._‚Ü≠_` is *not*
-- a thin relation ‚Äî `Perm.refl` and `Perm.trans Perm.refl Perm.refl`
-- are distinct constructors despite witnessing the same underlying
-- list permutation.  Concrete counter-example: `f = id`, `sf =
-- structural-id`, `g = id ‚àò id`, `sg = structural-‚àò structural-id
-- structural-id` give `Structural-to-perm sf = Perm.refl` while
-- `Structural-to-perm sg = Perm.trans Perm.refl Perm.refl`, which are
-- *not* `_‚â°_`, yet the corresponding hypergraphs are isomorphic.  So
-- the `perm-eq-from-iso` half could never be discharged as stated.
--
-- Reverting to a single postulate restores soundness: this is exactly
-- the statement of Mac Lane's symmetric monoidal coherence theorem on
-- the structural (i.e. generator-free) sub-language.  The constructive
-- discharge ultimately requires extending
-- `Categories.MonoidalCoherence.Solver` (currently Mac Lane only) to
-- handle œÉ via permutation tracking.
--
-- The constructive `Structural-to-perm` helper above is retained: it
-- is a useful and correct definition, and would feed into a future
-- model-theoretic discharge that interprets `FreeMonoidal` in a
-- category where structural morphisms are quotiented to bare list
-- permutations.

-- Splitting via `HasSigma?` exposes the œÉ-free (Mac Lane) sub-case as
-- a strictly narrower postulate that is mechanically dischargeable by
-- `Categories.MonoidalCoherence.Solver.solveM` once a variable-
-- indexing encoder is written (one Vec slot per distinct `Var x` atom
-- appearing in `A`/`B`).  The œÉ-containing residual is the genuine
-- remaining content ‚Äî requires extending `solveM` to the symmetric
-- fragment.  Under the iso hypothesis the œÉ-free case has identity-
-- forced boundary œÜ, so Mac Lane coherence applies directly.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Constructive discharge plumbing for the œÉ-free case via
-- `Categories.MonoidalCoherence.Solver.solveM`.
--
-- We instantiate the Solver at the *target* monoidal category
-- `(FreeMonoidal, Monoidal-FreeMonoidal)` itself: use it as a *proof*
-- tool, not as an evaluator into another category.  The Vec
-- `vars : Vec ObjTerm n` provides the per-atom mapping; atom `Fin i`
-- in the solver's `FreeMonoidal` interprets as `lookup vars i`, an
-- `ObjTerm` of the surrounding APROP free monoidal category.
--
-- Encoder pipeline (constructive parts below):
--   1. `objAtoms : ObjTerm ‚Üí List X` collects `Var x` atoms.
--   2. `idx : (xs : List X) (x : X) ‚Üí Fin (length xs)` lookup
--      (using `_‚âüX_`); on miss returns the last slot (safe fallback,
--      not used in the well-typed branch).
--   3. `varsOf : List X ‚Üí ‚àÉ Vec ObjTerm` produces the encoder's Vec.
--
-- Bridging the solver's `Fin n`-based `FreeMonoidal` back to the
-- surrounding APROP `FreeMonoidal` (which is over `X` with `Symm`
-- variant) requires `subst`-plumbing through two distinct
-- `FreeMonoidal` instantiations.  We leave the bridge as a narrow
-- postulate `enc-faithful` below ‚Äî strictly weaker than the original
-- `-noœÉ` claim because it is the *purely structural* soundness of the
-- Mac Lane encoder, no œÉ involved.

-- Collect `Var x` atoms from an ObjTerm.
objAtoms : ObjTerm ‚Üí List X
objAtoms unit     = []
objAtoms (A ‚äó‚ÇÄ B) = objAtoms A ++ objAtoms B
objAtoms (Var x)  = x ‚à∑ []

-- Index of x in xs (with safe fallback to `zero` of `Fin (suc (length xs))`).
idxFin : (xs : List X) (x : X) ‚Üí Fin (suc (length xs))
idxFin []       x = zero
idxFin (y ‚à∑ ys) x with x ‚âüX y
... | yes _ = zero
... | no  _ = suc (idxFin ys x)

-- Build a Vec of ObjTerm of length `suc (length xs)` from xs, padding
-- with `unit` at the sentinel slot.
varsVec : (xs : List X) ‚Üí Vec ObjTerm (suc (length xs))
varsVec []       = unit ‚à∑‚±Ω []‚±Ω
varsVec (x ‚à∑ xs) = Var x ‚à∑‚±Ω varsVec xs

-- Instantiate the Mac Lane coherence solver at the surrounding
-- FreeMonoidal, with the per-pair Vec `varsVec (xsAll f g)`.
module _ {A B : ObjTerm} {f g : HomTerm A B} (nf : NoSigma f) (ng : NoSigma g) where

  -- Atoms that need to be in the Vec: those from A, B, and any
  -- intermediate types inside f, g.  For the Mac Lane fragment a
  -- conservative choice is `objAtoms A ++ objAtoms B` extended with
  -- atoms collected from each NoSigma sub-term's type indices.

  -- We collect via NoSigma so termination is on the structural witness.
  nosigmaAtoms : ‚àÄ {A B} {h : HomTerm A B} ‚Üí NoSigma h ‚Üí List X
  nosigmaAtoms {A} {B} nosigma-id      = objAtoms A
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-Œª‚áí {A'})       = objAtoms A'
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-Œª‚áê {A'})       = objAtoms A'
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-œÅ‚áí {A'})       = objAtoms A'
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-œÅ‚áê {A'})       = objAtoms A'
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-Œ±‚áí {A'} {B'} {C'}) =
    objAtoms A' ++ objAtoms B' ++ objAtoms C'
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-Œ±‚áê {A'} {B'} {C'}) =
    objAtoms A' ++ objAtoms B' ++ objAtoms C'
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-‚àò h k) = nosigmaAtoms h ++ nosigmaAtoms k
  nosigmaAtoms (nosigma-‚äó h k) = nosigmaAtoms h ++ nosigmaAtoms k

  xsAll : List X
  xsAll = objAtoms A ++ objAtoms B ++ nosigmaAtoms nf ++ nosigmaAtoms ng

  vars-fg : Vec ObjTerm (suc (length xsAll))
  vars-fg = varsVec xsAll

  -- Instantiate the Mac Lane coherence solver in the surrounding
  -- FreeMonoidal, using `vars-fg` as the per-atom interpretation.
  open import Categories.MonoidalCoherence using (module Solver)
  open import Categories.Category.Monoidal using (Monoidal)
  open Monoidal Monoidal-FreeMonoidal using () renaming () public

  module S = Solver
    record { U = FreeMonoidal ; monoidal = Monoidal-FreeMonoidal }
    {n = suc (length xsAll)} vars-fg


  -- Structural encoder: ObjTerm ‚Üí S.ObjTerm.  Atoms are indexed via
  -- `idxFin xsAll`; the sentinel slot (`unit`) catches misses but
  -- well-typed encoding never lands there.
  enc-Obj : ObjTerm ‚Üí S.ObjTerm
  enc-Obj unit     = S.unit
  enc-Obj (P ‚äó‚ÇÄ Q) = enc-Obj P S.‚äó‚ÇÄ enc-Obj Q
  enc-Obj (Var x)  = S.Var (idxFin xsAll x)

  -- Structural encoder on HomTerms: NoSigma ‚Üí S.HomTerm.  Defined by
  -- structural recursion on the `NoSigma` witness; each clause maps
  -- the APROP-side constructor to its solver-side counterpart.
  enc-Hom : ‚àÄ {P Q} {h : HomTerm P Q}
          ‚Üí NoSigma h
          ‚Üí S.HomTerm (enc-Obj P) (enc-Obj Q)
  enc-Hom nosigma-id      = S.id
  enc-Hom nosigma-Œª‚áí      = S.Œª‚áí
  enc-Hom nosigma-Œª‚áê      = S.Œª‚áê
  enc-Hom nosigma-œÅ‚áí      = S.œÅ‚áí
  enc-Hom nosigma-œÅ‚áê      = S.œÅ‚áê
  enc-Hom nosigma-Œ±‚áí      = S.Œ±‚áí
  enc-Hom nosigma-Œ±‚áê      = S.Œ±‚áê
  enc-Hom (nosigma-‚àò h k) = enc-Hom h S.‚àò enc-Hom k
  enc-Hom (nosigma-‚äó h k) = enc-Hom h S.‚äó‚ÇÅ enc-Hom k

  -- The Solver's interpretation `‚ü¶ ef ‚üß‚ÇÅ` lives in APROP's
  -- FreeMonoidal: source `Functor.F‚ÇÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj P) : ObjTerm`, target similarly.
  -- `solveM ef eg : ‚ü¶ ef ‚üß‚ÇÅ ‚âàTerm ‚ü¶ eg ‚üß‚ÇÅ` is precisely an APROP-side
  -- `_‚âàTerm_` equation (Mac Lane coherence in the œÉ-free fragment).
  --
  -- To convert this into `f ‚âàTerm g`, we need encoder-soundness:
  -- `f ‚âàTerm Functor.F‚ÇÅ S.freeFunctor (enc-Hom nf)` and similarly for `g` (modulo
  -- equality `Functor.F‚ÇÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj A) ‚â° A`).  Both lemmas are pure structural
  -- recursions, but discharging them requires bridging two
  -- `FreeMonoidal` instantiations and aligning `subst`s ‚Äî left as a
  -- narrow self-contained postulate.

  -- Encoded pair (constructive output of the encoder).
  ef-built : S.HomTerm (enc-Obj A) (enc-Obj B)
  ef-built = enc-Hom nf

  eg-built : S.HomTerm (enc-Obj A) (enc-Obj B)
  eg-built = enc-Hom ng

  -- `solveM` discharges Mac Lane coherence in the œÉ-free Fin-indexed
  -- FreeMonoidal.  The return type uses the Solver's private
  -- `FreeFunctor` interpretation `‚ü¶_‚üß‚ÇÅ` (not re-exported by `Solver`
  -- with `public`).  We name the result and let Agda infer the type.
  --
  -- This call is the *constructive heart* of the œÉ-free coherence
  -- discharge: at this point all the categorical work is done.  The
  -- remaining work (`enc-bridge-to-f‚âàg`) is purely the encoder's
  -- soundness reflection back into APROP's `_‚âàTerm_`.
  solver-result : _
  solver-result = S.solveM ef-built eg-built

  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  -- Encoder soundness: `Functor.F‚ÇÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj P) ‚â° P` when atoms of P live in xsAll.
  --
  -- Below, `lookup-mem` is the heart: when `x ‚àà xs` (witnessed by `Any`),
  -- the encoder round-trips `x` to `Var x`.  Then `enc-Obj-sound` is a
  -- straight structural induction on `P`, using `lookup-mem` at each
  -- `Var` leaf.

  -- Helper: lookup at the index produced by `idxFin` round-trips through
  -- the var-vector.  By induction on the membership witness.
  lookup-mem
    : (xs : List X) {x : X} (m : x ‚àà xs)
    ‚Üí lookup (varsVec xs) (idxFin xs x) ‚â° Var x
  lookup-mem (y ‚à∑ ys) {x} (here refl) with x ‚âüX y
  ... | yes _    = refl
  ... | no  x‚â¢y  = ‚ä•-elim (x‚â¢y refl)
  lookup-mem (y ‚à∑ ys) {x} (there m) with x ‚âüX y
  ... | yes refl = refl
  ... | no  _    = lookup-mem ys m

  -- A `Var` atom appearing inside `objAtoms P` is exactly an atom of P.
  -- For our use we need to convert "every atom of P is in xsAll" into
  -- the relevant membership witness.  We work with the simple sublist
  -- inclusion `objAtoms P ‚äÜ xsAll`.

  _‚äÜL_ : List X ‚Üí List X ‚Üí Set
  xs ‚äÜL ys = ‚àÄ {x} ‚Üí x ‚àà xs ‚Üí x ‚àà ys

  -- Soundness of the object encoder, parameterised by membership.
  enc-Obj-sound
    : (P : ObjTerm)
    ‚Üí objAtoms P ‚äÜL xsAll
    ‚Üí Functor.F‚ÇÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj P) ‚â° P
  enc-Obj-sound unit       _   = refl
  enc-Obj-sound (P ‚äó‚ÇÄ Q) sub =
    cong‚ÇÇ _‚äó‚ÇÄ_
      (enc-Obj-sound P (Œª m ‚Üí sub (‚àà-++À° m)))
      (enc-Obj-sound Q (Œª m ‚Üí sub (‚àà-++ ≥ (objAtoms P) m)))
    where
      ‚àà-++À° : ‚àÄ {x ys zs} ‚Üí x ‚àà ys ‚Üí x ‚àà (ys ++ zs)
      ‚àà-++À° (here px)  = here px
      ‚àà-++À° (there m)  = there (‚àà-++À° m)
      ‚àà-++ ≥ : ‚àÄ {x} (ys : List X) {zs} ‚Üí x ‚àà zs ‚Üí x ‚àà (ys ++ zs)
      ‚àà-++ ≥ []        m = m
      ‚àà-++ ≥ (y ‚à∑ ys') m = there (‚àà-++ ≥ ys' m)
  enc-Obj-sound (Var x) sub = lookup-mem xsAll (sub (here refl))

  -- xsAll begins with `objAtoms A`, so atoms of A are trivially in xsAll.
  -- Similarly, after the A-prefix it has objAtoms B, then the two
  -- nosigmaAtoms blocks.

  ‚àà-++À° : ‚àÄ {x} {ys zs : List X} ‚Üí x ‚àà ys ‚Üí x ‚àà (ys ++ zs)
  ‚àà-++À° (here px)  = here px
  ‚àà-++À° (there m)  = there (‚àà-++À° m)
  ‚àà-++ ≥ : ‚àÄ {x} (ys : List X) {zs : List X} ‚Üí x ‚àà zs ‚Üí x ‚àà (ys ++ zs)
  ‚àà-++ ≥ []        m = m
  ‚àà-++ ≥ (y ‚à∑ ys') m = there (‚àà-++ ≥ ys' m)

  -- objAtoms A is the first block of xsAll.
  A-atoms-in-xsAll : objAtoms A ‚äÜL xsAll
  A-atoms-in-xsAll m = ‚àà-++À° m

  B-atoms-in-xsAll : objAtoms B ‚äÜL xsAll
  B-atoms-in-xsAll m = ‚àà-++ ≥ (objAtoms A) (‚àà-++À° m)

  enc-Obj-sound-A : Functor.F‚ÇÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj A) ‚â° A
  enc-Obj-sound-A = enc-Obj-sound A A-atoms-in-xsAll

  enc-Obj-sound-B : Functor.F‚ÇÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj B) ‚â° B
  enc-Obj-sound-B = enc-Obj-sound B B-atoms-in-xsAll

  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  -- Inclusion of every NoSigma sub-term's atoms into xsAll.  We thread
  -- this as a `Path` from a witness inside `nf`/`ng` down to xsAll.
  --
  -- For ‚àò/‚äó we use the fact that `nosigmaAtoms` is additive across
  -- composition/tensor (the witness lives in either the left or right
  -- branch).  But really, only the LEAF nodes need direct membership ‚Äî
  -- internal ‚àò/‚äó nodes inherit recursively.  We therefore phrase
  -- `enc-Hom-sound` as: given that the source and target objAtoms are
  -- in xsAll, the encoder is sound; and at ‚àò/‚äó we recurse with the
  -- intermediate type's atoms in xsAll (provided by the structural
  -- shape of nf, ng).

  -- For `nosigma-‚àò {B = M} h k` we need atoms of M in xsAll.  In the
  -- `nf`/`ng` witnesses, the intermediate type M's atoms appear in the
  -- corresponding sub-term's nosigmaAtoms (every leaf inside h has type
  -- with M-related atoms covered).  Rather than thread the inclusion
  -- explicitly, we expose a structural-induction-friendly form that
  -- carries the source/target inclusions as parameters.

  --------------------------------------------------------------------------------
  -- Hom encoder soundness (‚âàTerm form, parameterised by atom-inclusions
  -- for the source and target types).
  --
  -- We package `Functor.F‚ÇÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj P) ‚â° P` and similarly for Q, then state:
  --
  --   subst‚ÇÇ HomTerm sP sQ (Functor.F‚ÇÅ S.freeFunctor (enc-Hom nh)) ‚â° h
  --
  -- By induction on nh.  Base cases are immediate because
  -- `S.‚ü¶ S.id ‚üß‚ÇÅ`, `S.‚ü¶ S.Œª‚áí ‚üß‚ÇÅ`, ..., reduce definitionally to the
  -- APROP-side constructors `id`, `Œª‚áí`, ..., at the encoded source/
  -- target objects.  The `subst‚ÇÇ` collapses to `refl` after K-style
  -- reasoning on ObjTerm equality (justified by ObjTerm having
  -- decidable equality, hence UIP).

  -- For the ‚àò/‚äó inductive cases we additionally need atom-inclusion
  -- for the intermediate type; these come from the structural form
  -- of the NoSigma sub-witness's source/target leaves.

  -- We expose only the specialised forms we need: encoder soundness
  -- specifically at f and at g (both `HomTerm A B`).  Their proofs use
  -- the postulate `enc-Hom-‚â°-up-to-subst` below ‚Äî the *narrowest*
  -- remaining gap, strictly about `subst` plumbing through a
  -- definitionally-trivial encoder.

  postulate
    -- Narrow encoder-soundness postulate: any NoSigma term h is
    -- transported to itself by the encoder‚Äìdecoder round-trip.  This
    -- is strictly narrower than `-noœÉ`: it asserts no categorical
    -- equation, only that the encoder is the *identity-on-NoSigma-
    -- terms* up to the obvious type transport.  Discharging it
    -- amounts to UIP on ObjTerm (provable from decidable atom
    -- equality) plus the definitional reductions of `S.‚ü¶_‚üß‚ÇÅ` on each
    -- constructor.
    enc-Hom-sound-id
      : ‚àÄ {P Q} {h : HomTerm P Q} (nh : NoSigma h)
        (sP : Functor.F‚ÇÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj P) ‚â° P) (sQ : Functor.F‚ÇÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj Q) ‚â° Q)
      ‚Üí subst‚ÇÇ HomTerm sP sQ (Functor.F‚ÇÅ S.freeFunctor (enc-Hom nh)) ‚â° h

  -- Lift the propositional encoder-soundness into ‚âàTerm.
  enc-Hom-sound-‚âà
    : ‚àÄ {P Q} {h : HomTerm P Q} (nh : NoSigma h)
      (sP : Functor.F‚ÇÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj P) ‚â° P) (sQ : Functor.F‚ÇÄ S.freeFunctor (enc-Obj Q) ‚â° Q)
    ‚Üí subst‚ÇÇ HomTerm sP sQ (Functor.F‚ÇÅ S.freeFunctor (enc-Hom nh)) ‚âàTerm h
  enc-Hom-sound-‚âà nh sP sQ
    rewrite enc-Hom-sound-id nh sP sQ = ‚âà-Term-refl

  -- The discharge of the œÉ-free Structural coherence postulate:
  -- combine encoder soundness with `solver-result`.  All three pieces
  -- live in `HomTerm A B` after the subst-transports of
  -- `enc-Obj-sound-{A,B}`.

  noœÉ-discharge : f ‚âàTerm g
  noœÉ-discharge = ‚âà-Term-trans (‚âà-Term-sym sound-f)
                   (‚âà-Term-trans subst-eq sound-g)
    where
      sP = enc-Obj-sound-A
      sQ = enc-Obj-sound-B

      sound-f : subst‚ÇÇ HomTerm sP sQ (Functor.F‚ÇÅ S.freeFunctor (enc-Hom nf)) ‚âàTerm f
      sound-f = enc-Hom-sound-‚âà nf sP sQ

      sound-g : subst‚ÇÇ HomTerm sP sQ (Functor.F‚ÇÅ S.freeFunctor (enc-Hom ng)) ‚âàTerm g
      sound-g = enc-Hom-sound-‚âà ng sP sQ

      -- Push solver-result through subst‚ÇÇ: subst‚ÇÇ is a congruence
      -- for ‚âàTerm (with the same indices on both sides).
      subst‚ÇÇ-cong-‚âàTerm
        : ‚àÄ {P Q P' Q'} (eP : P ‚â° P') (eQ : Q ‚â° Q')
          {h k : HomTerm P Q} ‚Üí h ‚âàTerm k
        ‚Üí subst‚ÇÇ HomTerm eP eQ h ‚âàTerm subst‚ÇÇ HomTerm eP eQ k
      subst‚ÇÇ-cong-‚âàTerm refl refl eq = eq

      subst-eq
        : subst‚ÇÇ HomTerm sP sQ (Functor.F‚ÇÅ S.freeFunctor (enc-Hom nf))
        ‚âàTerm subst‚ÇÇ HomTerm sP sQ (Functor.F‚ÇÅ S.freeFunctor (enc-Hom ng))
      subst-eq = subst‚ÇÇ-cong-‚âàTerm sP sQ solver-result

-- Discharge of the previously-postulated œÉ-free coherence claim, now
-- via the module-internal `noœÉ-discharge`.

Structural-coherence-‚âàTerm-noœÉ
  : ‚àÄ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
  ‚Üí NoSigma f ‚Üí NoSigma g
  ‚Üí ‚ü™ f ‚ü´ ‚âÖ·¥¥ ‚ü™ g ‚ü´
  ‚Üí f ‚âàTerm g
Structural-coherence-‚âàTerm-noœÉ {f = f} {g = g} nf ng _ = noœÉ-discharge nf ng

postulate
  Structural-coherence-‚âàTerm-œÉ
    : ‚àÄ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
    ‚Üí Structural f ‚Üí Structural g
    ‚Üí ‚ü™ f ‚ü´ ‚âÖ·¥¥ ‚ü™ g ‚ü´
    ‚Üí f ‚âàTerm g

-- Dispatch: œÉ-free √ó œÉ-free goes to the Mac Lane sub-postulate; any
-- œÉ-containing pair goes to the symmetric residual.
Structural-coherence-‚âàTerm
  : ‚àÄ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
  ‚Üí Structural f ‚Üí Structural g
  ‚Üí ‚ü™ f ‚ü´ ‚âÖ·¥¥ ‚ü™ g ‚ü´
  ‚Üí f ‚âàTerm g
Structural-coherence-‚âàTerm sf sg iso with HasSigma? sf | HasSigma? sg
... | inj‚ÇÅ nf | inj‚ÇÅ ng = Structural-coherence-‚âàTerm-noœÉ nf ng iso
... | _       | _       = Structural-coherence-‚âàTerm-œÉ   sf sg iso

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Derived: lift `Structural-coherence-‚âàTerm` through `bridge` and
-- `decode-roundtrip-rel` to the original `decode-rel`-shaped lemma.
--
-- The derivation is purely categorical (no further postulates): the
-- `bridge`-wrapping is a congruence with respect to `_‚âàTerm_`, and
-- `decode-rel f ‚âàTerm bridge f` for every `f` by `decode-roundtrip-rel`.

private
  open import Categories.Category using (Category)
  module FM = Category FreeMonoidal
  open FM.HomReasoning

  -- `bridge` is a congruence for `_‚âàTerm_`.  Inlined here so the
  -- discharge module doesn't depend on the `DecodeRoundtrip` private
  -- helper.
  bridge-resp-‚âàTerm
    : ‚àÄ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
    ‚Üí f ‚âàTerm g ‚Üí bridge f ‚âàTerm bridge g
  bridge-resp-‚âàTerm f‚âàg = refl‚ü©‚àò‚ü® f‚âàg ‚ü©‚àò‚ü®refl

Structural-coherence
  : ‚àÄ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
  ‚Üí Structural f ‚Üí Structural g
  ‚Üí ‚ü™ f ‚ü´ ‚âÖ·¥¥ ‚ü™ g ‚ü´
  ‚Üí decode-rel f ‚âàTerm decode-rel g
Structural-coherence {f = f} {g = g} sf sg iso = begin
  decode-rel f   ‚âà‚ü® decode-roundtrip-rel f ‚ü©
  bridge f       ‚âà‚ü® bridge-resp-‚âàTerm (Structural-coherence-‚âàTerm sf sg iso) ‚ü©
  bridge g       ‚âà‚ü® decode-roundtrip-rel g ‚ü®
  decode-rel g   ‚àé

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
-- Discharge the original postulate.
--
-- `Atomic f` + `nE ‚ü™ f ‚ü´ ‚â° 0` ‚áí `Structural f` (rules out `Agen`).
-- For the atomic shapes routed into the `‚Ä¶-0E` case from
-- `AtomicCompound.dispatch-structural`, the atomic-side edge count is
-- 0 by construction (see `nE-{id,Œª‚áí,Œª‚áê,œÅ‚áí,œÅ‚áê,Œ±‚áí,Œ±‚áê,œÉ}` there) ‚Äî we
-- recover that here by case-splitting on the `Atomic` witness rather
-- than threading the edge-count proof through the API.

-- The originally-postulated lemma.  Note: the `Atomic f` hypothesis
-- combined with the dispatch from `AtomicCompound.dispatch-structural`
-- guarantees that `f` is *not* `Agen` (the Agen branch routes to
-- `decode-rel-resp-‚âÖ·¥¥-Agen-compound-1E` instead).  We extract a
-- `Structural f` witness by case-analysis on `Atomic f`, where the
-- `Agen` branch is dismissed via the iso witness's edge-count
-- transport (a `Fin 1 ‚Üî Fin 0` contradiction).

-- The discharge of `decode-rel-resp-‚âÖ·¥¥-atomic-compound-0E`.  Note we
-- *drop* the redundant `Compound g` hypothesis: under
-- `nE ‚ü™ g ‚ü´ ‚â° 0`, the `Compound g` argument carries no information
-- beyond the boundary types, since `Structural g` is recovered from
-- the edge-count witness alone (see `nE-0‚ÜíStructural`).  Dropping it
-- breaks an otherwise-circular import between `AtomicCompound.agda`
-- (which defines `Compound`) and this module.  The caller in
-- `AtomicCompound.agda` ignores the redundant argument when wiring up.

decode-rel-resp-‚âÖ·¥¥-atomic-compound-0E
  : ‚àÄ {A B} {f g : HomTerm A B}
  ‚Üí Atomic f
  ‚Üí nE ‚ü™ g ‚ü´ ‚â° 0
  ‚Üí ‚ü™ f ‚ü´ ‚âÖ·¥¥ ‚ü™ g ‚ü´
  ‚Üí decode-rel f ‚âàTerm decode-rel g
decode-rel-resp-‚âÖ·¥¥-atomic-compound-0E {f = f} {g = g} af g-nE‚â°0 iso =
  Structural-coherence
    (atomic‚Üístructural af)
    (nE-0‚ÜíStructural g g-nE‚â°0)
    iso
  where
    -- The `Agen` branch of `Atomic f` is incompatible with
    -- `‚ü™ f ‚ü´ ‚âÖ·¥¥ ‚ü™ g ‚ü´` when `nE ‚ü™ g ‚ü´ ‚â° 0`: the iso induces a
    -- bijection `Fin 1 ‚Üî Fin 0`, which is absurd.  We discharge it by
    -- routing `œà : Fin (nE ‚ü™ Agen _ ‚ü´) ‚Üí Fin (nE ‚ü™ g ‚ü´)` and then
    -- transporting along `nE ‚ü™ g ‚ü´ ‚â° 0`.
    open import Data.Fin using (Fin; zero)
    open import Relation.Binary.PropositionalEquality using (subst; sym)

    Fin-zero-empty : Fin 0 ‚Üí ‚ä•
    Fin-zero-empty ()

    -- In the `Agen` branch of `Atomic f`, the original `iso :
    -- ‚ü™ f ‚ü´ ‚âÖ·¥¥ ‚ü™ g ‚ü´` becomes `‚ü™ Agen h ‚ü´ ‚âÖ·¥¥ ‚ü™ g ‚ü´` (with
    -- `nE ‚ü™ Agen h ‚ü´ ‚â° 1`), so `œà zero : Fin (nE ‚ü™ g ‚ü´) = Fin 0`.
    atomic‚Üístructural : Atomic f ‚Üí Structural f
    atomic‚Üístructural (atomic-Agen h) =
      ‚ä•-elim (Fin-zero-empty (subst Fin g-nE‚â°0 (_‚âÖ·¥¥_.œà iso zero)))
    atomic‚Üístructural atomic-id        = structural-id
    atomic‚Üístructural atomic-Œª‚áí        = structural-Œª‚áí
    atomic‚Üístructural atomic-Œª‚áê        = structural-Œª‚áê
    atomic‚Üístructural atomic-œÅ‚áí        = structural-œÅ‚áí
    atomic‚Üístructural atomic-œÅ‚áê        = structural-œÅ‚áê
